SJR91 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 SJR___ NAMING BOTH BRIDGES ON INTERSTATE 22 THAT SPANS
5 MULBERRY FORK IN WALKER COUNTY, ALABAMA, THE SENATOR GREG
6 REED BRIDGE.
7
8 WHEREAS, it is with the highest accolade that this
9 body honors Senator Greg Reed by requesting the State
10 Department of Transportation designate both bridges on
11 Interstate 22 that span Mulberry Fork in Walker County,
12 Alabama, as Senator Greg Reed Bridge; one bridge runs
13 southeast while its companion runs northwest; and
14 WHEREAS, Senator Greg Reed was born in Jasper and
15 grew up in Cordova in Walker County; he graduated from
16 Walker County public schools and attended Walker College,
17 now Bevill State Community College; he earned his bachelor's
18 degree from The University of Alabama; and
19 WHEREAS, Senator Greg Reed's career in public service
20 began in 2010, when he was elected to the Alabama Senate; he
21 was reelected in 2014 and 2018; his Republican colleagues
22 elected him Majority Leader at the start of the new
23 legislative term in 2015; in 2021, he served as the Alabama
24 Senate's President Pro Tempore with integrity and
25 distinction until November 2024 when he joined Kay Ivey's
26 administration as Senior Advisor to Workforce
27 Transformation; and
28 WHEREAS, Senator Greg Reed focused his sponsored
Page 1

WHEREAS, Senator Greg Reed focused his sponsored
SJR91 Enrolled
29 legislation on Medicaid reform, economic development,
30 workforce transformation, and rural enhancement; key 2024
31 legislation included the "Working for Alabama" package, the
32 Alabama Growth Alliance Act, and education-related
33 transparency, which boosted workforce participation and
34 rural development; he continues to greatly impact the
35 success of Alabama's workforce in his current role as
36 Secretary of the Department of Workforce; now therefore,
37 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
38 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That to honor former Alabama
39 Senator Greg Reed, who served the State of Alabama with
40 integrity and distinction as a legislator and continues to
41 positively impact the state's workforce as the first
42 Secretary of the Department of Workforce, the State
43 Department of Transportation is encouraged to coordinate
44 with local governing officials to consider designating both
45 bridges on Interstate 22 that span Mulberry Fork in Walker
46 County, Alabama, the Senator Greg Reed Bridge and to erect
47 appropriate signs or markers, consistent with applicable
48 requirements and laws, in recognition of this designation.
